@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
'
' Objective-side use cases for the /mdd-deploy utility skill. STANDALONE,
' a sibling of /mdd-render: NOT wired into /mdd-cycle, /mdd-map,
' /mdd-validate, or /mdd-review; never executes a deploy command.
'
' CHANGE (this cycle): /mdd-deploy gains a second IaC dialect. The
' operator picks ONE dialect per run — Bicep XOR Terraform — and that
' choice MUST be explicitly confirmed via a blocking pause BEFORE any
' deploy artifact (diagram.puml, runbook.md, or generated IaC) is
' written. There is NO silent default: even Bicep, implicit today, now
' requires the confirmation. Both dialects enforce the SAME invariant
' checklist and the SAME secure-by-default network posture (full
' parity); only the generated IaC structure differs.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Operator runs /mdd-deploy with a one-line deployment description; the skill produces a UML deployment diagram, secure-by-default generated IaC in the CONFIRMED dialect (Bicep XOR Terraform — one per run, no silent default), and an explicit copy-pasteable runbook that preserves the target's security invariants identically for either dialect. It pauses with a blocking clarification on ambiguity, on any statically detectable go-live landmine, AND — new — to confirm the IaC dialect before writing anything. The skill executes nothing — the human runs the commands.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Operator inspects the generated deployment diagram visually: /mdd-render also rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive and non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT, "Before any deploy artifact is created, /mdd-deploy resolves the requested IaC dialect from the description (Bicep or Terraform), presents it back, and BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation — the same discipline as the landmine pause. No silent default: an unconfirmed or unspecified dialect halts the skill before diagram.puml / runbook.md / generated IaC are written. Exactly one dialect per run; Terraform enforces the same invariants + secure-by-default posture as Bicep, differing only in structure (main.tf + modules + azurerm provider + remote state backend).")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform) before any\nartifact is written — no silent default" as Dialect
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  v1 target: azure-container-apps (../atlas-ate-server).
  Reads .mdd/models + the target repo READ-ONLY.
  PAUSES with a BLOCKING clarification on ambiguity OR
  a statically detectable go-live landmine — same
  discipline as /mdd-cycle, never a buried runbook
  STOP note. Writes the deployment diagram + runbook
  + SECURE-BY-DEFAULT generated IaC in the confirmed
  dialect (no store left more network-open than its
  peers; migrations-before-traffic stays a documented
  procedural tradeoff); then reports and STOPS.
  NEVER runs az / docker / terraform / brew.
  Diagram stereotypes are DOCUMENTATION ONLY.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Dialect
  Mandatory <<include>>: guidance cannot proceed until
  the dialect is explicitly confirmed. One dialect per
  run (Bicep XOR Terraform). FULL PARITY — both
  dialects enforce the identical invariant checklist
  and secure-by-default posture; only IaC structure
  differs. Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
